As more Oracle eBS code uses Java and the source code is not available as used to be with other tools (i.e Oracle Forms, PL/SQL), there is a need to be able to decompile .class files. One tool that I find particularly useful when needed is <a href="http://java.decompiler.free.fr/?q=jdgui" target="_blank">JD-GUI</a>, which is free for non-commercial use.